<h2 id="perform-initial-migration" sourcefile="includes/mvc-intro/adding-model2xp.md" sourcestartlinenumber="2" sourceendlinenumber="2">Perform initial migration</h2>
<p sourcefile="includes/mvc-intro/adding-model2xp.md" sourcestartlinenumber="4" sourceendlinenumber="4">From the command line, run the following .NET Core CLI commands:</p>
<pre sourcefile="includes/mvc-intro/adding-model2xp.md" sourcestartlinenumber="6" sourceendlinenumber="9"><code class="lang-console">dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate
dotnet ef database update
</code></pre><p sourcefile="includes/mvc-intro/adding-model2xp.md" sourcestartlinenumber="11" sourceendlinenumber="11">The <code>dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate</code> command generates code to create the initial database schema. The schema is based on the model specified in the <code>DbContext</code> (In the <em>Models/MovieContext.cs</em> file). The <code>Initial</code> argument is used to name the migrations. You can use any name, but by convention you choose a name that describes the migration. See <a class="xref" href="../../data/ef-mvc/migrations.html#introduction-to-migrations" data-raw-source="[Introduction to migrations](xref:data/ef-mvc/migrations#introduction-to-migrations)" sourcefile="includes/mvc-intro/adding-model2xp.md" sourcestartlinenumber="11" sourceendlinenumber="11">Introduction to migrations</a> for more information.</p>
<p sourcefile="includes/mvc-intro/adding-model2xp.md" sourcestartlinenumber="13" sourceendlinenumber="13">The <code>dotnet ef database update</code> command runs the <code>Up</code> method in the <em>Migrations/&lt;time-stamp&gt;_InitialCreate.cs</em> file, which creates the database.</p>
